<br>
There is no mens rea to libel or slander, your state of mind and whether you believed what you posted was true or not does not matter - the fact that you made a post intended to defame another (which you have admitted that you did) constitutes libel.  <br>
<br>
If I post that a person is a ninja looter with the intent to defame them or hurt their reputation, then I have committed libel whether or not my accusation is true.  The defamatory nature of the writing is all that you look at for the first test.  The next question is whether the writing is libelous (or slanderous if you are dealing with the spoken word).  This basically means you look to see if the person about whom the writing was made was harmed by the writing - which basically goes to the &quot;truth&quot; of what was published.  It is typically said that truth is an absolute bar for any slander or libel claim and this is accurate - but you have also admitted that you didnt know at the time you made the original post whether it was true or not, and now admit that the post was untrue, which makes the original post both libel and libelous - and it makes you at fault for both whether you actually knew what you were posting was false or not.<br>
<br>
News media typically avoid libel in a variety of ways when a story that is clearly negative has been reported.  They cite the source of the information and lay the blame on them.  While not always enough, if ABC reports that NBC has reported that Barry Bonds uses steroids - then NBC would have committed libel (for publishing an article on BB steroid use) while ABC would not (because they reported factually that NBC reported that BB used steroids).  On the other hand, if ABC said sources report or informed media sources report or anything else short of naming the source of the report that BB used steroids, then ABC would be committing libel.<br>
<br>
I think that Mipp was correct generally when he said you committed slander (although it was technically libel) and I think that you are attempting to cover your idiotic post and cloud your mistake by making weak political attacks to justify your position even though it is unreasonable.<br>
<br>
Finally, the fact that you failed to edit your original post to delete the falsehoods entirely, but instead left the libelous portions after you knew they were false shows a great deal of pettiness - either in getting caught in a lie and in attempting to cover your own mistakes, or in trying to convince people through falsehood that your political agenda is the correct one.<br>
<br>
