<br>
<br>
Not entirely true.  From one of the many Web authorities (emphasis is mine):<br>
<br>
What is Libel?<br>
Definitions <br>
<br>
Libel is the publication of a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  false</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> statement which injures a person's business or personal reputation. <br>
<br>
In order to be libelous, a statement must meet these conditions:<br>
<br>
There must be some negligence on the part of the writer <br>
It must be defamatory (<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  false and injurious</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to the plaintiff's reputation) <br>
It must be published (distributed to someone other than the plaintiff and defendant) <br>
It is not privileged communication* <br>
The plaintiff must be identifiable to the reader <br>
 <br>
 ------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
In any event,  it was libelous..<br>
<br>
<br>
